                    <h3>Special Projects and Accomplishments</h3>
                    <p>Dr. Mowbray does extensive speaking and teaching in public conferences and forums.  His public tutorials and briefings have been presented at: INTEROP, OOPSLA, Object World, FedOOTS, Object Expo, CORBA Academy, IBM International Conference on Object Technology, Toward an Electronic Patient Record (TEPR), IEEE COMPSAC, and Patterns98.  Dr. Mowbray is  an advisor and tutorial presenter to consortium groups and standards bodies, including the Object Management Group, The National Industrial Information Infrastructure Project (NIIIP) Consortium, and the Open Geographic Information Systems Consortium (OGC).</p>

